In an astonishing reveal, it turns out that Cardi B and Offset got married last year. Celebrity newsite TMZ reports that the marriage was something she wanted to keep private. The showbiz couple got married on the 20 of September, 2017 at Fulton County, “There are so many moments that I share with the world and then there are moments that I want to keep for myself! Getting married was one of those moments! Our relationship was so new breaking up and making up and we had a lot of growing up to do but we was so in love we didn’t want to lose each other. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-672828 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/0622-cardi-b-offset-marriage-launch-5.jpg" alt="" width="1000" height="530" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/0622-cardi-b-offset-marriage-launch-5.jpg 728w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/0622-cardi-b-offset-marriage-launch-5-487x258.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/0622-cardi-b-offset-marriage-launch-5-320x170.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/0622-cardi-b-offset-marriage-launch-5-640x339.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/0622-cardi-b-offset-marriage-launch-5-600x318.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /> “I said I do, with no dress no makeup and no ring! I appreciate and love my husband so much for still wanting for me to have that special moment that every girl dreams of when he got down on his knee and put a ring on my finger and he did that for me!!”  She also wrote on Twitter that privacy is the reason why she named her album Invasion of Privacy  What can we say?